PREREQUISITE
============

- Text parsing library
- Polygon management library



HOW TO INSTALL
==============

1) with configure


$ ./configure [options]
$ make
# make install


Configure options:
 
 --prefix=INSTALL_DIR
    Install directory path.  If omitted, default is /usr/local/Cutlib.

 --host=hostname
    Specify in case of cross-compilation.


 CXX=CXX_COMPILER
    Specify a C++ compiler, e.g., g++, icpc, xlc++ or others.

 CXXFLAGS=CXX_OPTIONS
    Specify compiler options.


Here is examples.

$ ./configure --prefix=/usr/local/Cutlib CXX=icpc CXXFLAGS=-O3


$ ./configure --prefix=$1 \
              --host=sparc64-unknown-linux-gnu \
              CXX=mpiFCCpx \
              CXXFLAGS="-Kfast,ocl,preex,simd=2,uxsimd,array_private,parallel,openmp,optmsg=2"


If you try to install process again, execute 'make distclean' then configure.



2) Hand compile

Edit environmental variables in a Makefile_hand file for a target machine. Then, 'make'.   
A compiled module libCUT.a will be placed in $(CUT_DIR)/lib/ directory.

